metadata.name: Secret Garden #16
metadata.description:
Secret Garden

This secret garden, which does not exist anywhere else, is a secret space found in the brain of AI, that is, in the latent space. Would the AI ‚Äã‚Äãthat created these mysterious gardens have memories of the scent of flowers in its brain?
No matter how well a machine imitates the human learning process, it has inherent limitations. Humans remember the situation by comprehensively utilizing the five senses, including not only the visual information of the flowers, but also the melodies that flowed at that moment, the buzzing of flying bees, the dizzying scent of flowers, and the warm sunlight. However, this AI only does fractional numerical calculations using only the given pixel RGB values.

Humans with much more complex brains and computational systems are passionate about the images that AI creates. However, if you think about it a little, it seems that this interest may be a kind of leisurely relaxation for mature beings to watch the development of immature beings.
This AI doesn't even know what it just built.


* Draw algorithmic strokes by reference the color of AI-generated flower garden.
* One of 832 AI-generated seed images are randomly selected.
* No property(traits), no rarity

[Left click on the screen] : add strokes (Temporarily retouching)
[S] Save to file

Made with Love & P5.js & P5.beizer !

By CSLIM, 2022

metadata.name: FairyCells #282
metadata.description:
FairyCells is a series created by a generative system, displaying shapes, between 1 and 10, made up of three different color palettes. 
Cells cannot cross each other, and are composed of a flat tint and/or a hatch system.

You can right-click to download an SVG file of the NFT or press ¬´¬†E¬†¬ª to export as png (3401x3401px)

Moreover, the digital version can exist as a physical piece.
Owning the NFT gives the right to order, in addition, a 30x30cm plotter drawing of it. More information about it here: https://nft.julienespagnon.fr/fairy-cells.
You can see some test examples plotted in the google form: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1FO3Umh49qmJApZAlQgZ46a2y421QYEWIW8r72nLrW4Q/edit

Work by Julien Espagnon - 2021/2022

metadata.name: Momentary #284
metadata.description:
Sometimes, life's troubles seem to be immense and endless. They make us run around in despair, helplessly looking in every direction in search of an answer.

It's tough to be in control of those situations until we understand that everything in our life is momentary, the good times are momentary and of course the bad ones.

We tend to forget that life finds its way and that we just need to hold enough to start to see a clear path to follow.

Life is momentary, the good times are momentary and of course the bad ones.

Hold enough.

There is a path to follow.

-------
WARNING
Please, have into consideration that this work requires some CPU power due to the number of points that needs to be drawn on the canvas. Depending on the hardware and work features, the drawing could take some seconds to some minutes to be finished. 
-------

metadata.name: FairyCells II #159
metadata.description:
FairyCells II is intended as a logical continuation of the first FairyCells series. By dropping the plotter drawing constraint, new perspectives for exploration appeared.
This is how these cells began to intertwine, live together, mutate and change color, like an evolving system.

What surprises me the most in this new series, is the stories appearing behind each new composition. See how these abstracts shapes can come to life and narrate us things through our imagination.

Each color palette takes us into a different world, drawing a very specific atmosphere.

As me, let yourself be carried away by these stories üí´ !

Artwork by Julien_Espagnon, 2022.

metadata.name: Diffusion Walks: Series 1 #75
metadata.description:
Diffusion Walks: Series 1

first of all, zoom in. then zoom out. more.

implemented a modified "Image Random Circular Walker" 
to use sharp, rotating lines and jagged spirals instead of circular lines
by breaking radius/direction/angle a little bit, increasing stroke speed, 
and utilizing my own finetuned diffusion model outputs as inits for the new walking algorithm.


The new walk is some what of a frantic spidercrawl, accompanied by a shimmering dance.
I enjoy the glints of frenzy that this sort of motion adds to otherwise serene diffusion outputs.
Furthermore, there's something special about the output being revealed; re-distorting a guided
set of denoised images gives a lot of depth and momentum to the work for me personally.
It turns the process into a cycle.

fxrand() affects the init image, stroke speed, number of strokes, duration, stroke angle, and stroke sequence direction.

there are 25 image variations.
this is not about the images as much as it is about the walk.
there are countless walk variations.

duration, stroke angle and direction ranges vary as well.

there are 6 potential speeds.

as a result, hash variations will affect clarity, palette, init, and pattern of the token.

no recorded hash-unique features/attributes are printed on the token as a guide
please experience each variation's infinte iterations as their own realm
explore the variations, find different speeds and walker paths, enjoy the boundless variety in this set


zoom out to see the full image. zoom in for strokes. open live for easier zoom experience.
1280px by 1664px.

credits are important. when you play with a lot of things you made
mix them with things your friends made
and break things other people made
it is paramount to give all parties their flowers once
the art is made.

generated with my finetuned SD model, deforum notebook, and p5.js
credit to Vamoss for the original image walker algorithm (https://openprocessing.org/sketch/624879)
which was the basis for the new walker algo
credit to Stable-Diffusion team for original model which I tuned
credit to deforum team (which includes myself) for the deforum notebook

License included in License.md and p5.js file
License for Image Random Circular Walker and Diffusion Walks are both CC BY-SA 3.0

metadata.name: tratti #282
metadata.description:
"tratti" is an Italian word that has many different meanings. When we started working on this piece, we wanted to create something that combines our traits ("tratti" in Italian).
We had this urge to channel the turbulent times we're living in now into this artwork using just lines ("tratti" in Italian).

We don't know what to do now, we're here, and that's all that matters. We're here for our families, our friends, and our community. Like everything in life, there are joyful times and challenging times. We must accept happiness as something that is not constant but that we feel at times (a "tratti" in Italian).

With "tratti", we want to send a message to every disheartened human being: "Stay strong and never let anyone or anything crush the hope in you. Joyful times are around the corner".
